.TH MAN 1 "2026-06-01" "1.0.0" "Zensical Documentation Skills"
.SH NAME
man \- display man pages for Zensical documentation skills
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B man
.I skill-name
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B man
is a skill that displays manual pages for Zensical documentation skills.
Each skill stores its man page at
.IR ~/.config/opencode/skills/<skill>/man/<skill>.1 .
.PP
If the requested skill has no man page,
.B man
falls back to displaying the skill's
.I SKILL.md
file.
.SH USAGE
.TP
.BI "man " skill-name
Show the man page for the named skill.
.PP
Examples:
.IP
.B man glossary-sync
.IP
.B man frontmatterer
.IP
.B man man
.SH MAN PAGE CONVENTION
.PP
Every skill can optionally include a man page in standard troff format
using the man macro package. The file must be located at:
.IP
~/.config/opencode/skills/<skill>/man/<skill>.<section>
.PP
The default section is 1 (user commands). Section 7 (miscellaneous) may
be used for skills that are not command-style.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/opencode/skills/<skill>/man/<skill>.1
Man page for the skill.
.TP
.I ~/.config/opencode/skills/<skill>/SKILL.md
Fallback if no man page exists.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR glossary-sync (1),
.BR frontmatterer (1),
.BR permalink\-generator (1)
